The paper deals with an algorithmic problem in graph theory, specifically online bipartite matching with replacements. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT). The analysis of the algorithm involves combinatorics and optimization, which are also covered by discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the paper mentions information theory (cs.IT) in the context of communication complexity lower bounds.
